837 /* It looks odd for vlan_tci, vlan_vid, and vlan_pcp to say that they are
838  * supported in OF1.0 and OF1.1, since the detailed semantics of these fields
839  * only apply to NXM or OXM. They are marked as supported for exact matches in
840  * OF1.0 and OF1.1 because exact matches on those fields can be successfully
841  * translated into the OF1.0 and OF1.1 flow formats. */
842 
843  /* "vlan_tci".
844  *
845  * 802.1Q TCI.
846  *
847  * For a packet with an 802.1Q header, this is the Tag Control Information
848  * (TCI) field, with the CFI bit forced to 1. For a packet with no 802.1Q
849  * header, this has value 0.
850  *
851  * This field can be used in various ways:
852  *
853  * - If it is not constrained at all, the nx_match matches packets
854  * without an 802.1Q header or with an 802.1Q header that has any TCI
855  * value.
856  *
857  * - Testing for an exact match with 0 matches only packets without an
858  * 802.1Q header.
859  *
860  * - Testing for an exact match with a TCI value with CFI=1 matches
861  * packets that have an 802.1Q header with a specified VID and PCP.
862  *
863  * - Testing for an exact match with a nonzero TCI value with CFI=0 does
864  * not make sense. The switch may reject this combination.
865  *
866  * - Testing with a specific VID and CFI=1, with nxm_mask=0x1fff, matches
867  * packets that have an 802.1Q header with that VID (and any PCP).
868  *
869  * - Testing with a specific PCP and CFI=1, with nxm_mask=0xf000, matches
870  * packets that have an 802.1Q header with that PCP (and any VID).
871  *
872  * - Testing with nxm_value=0, nxm_mask=0x0fff matches packets with no
873  * 802.1Q header or with an 802.1Q header with a VID of 0.
874  *
875  * - Testing with nxm_value=0, nxm_mask=0xe000 matches packets with no
876  * 802.1Q header or with an 802.1Q header with a PCP of 0.
877  *
878  * - Testing with nxm_value=0, nxm_mask=0xefff matches packets with no
879  * 802.1Q header or with an 802.1Q header with both VID and PCP of 0.
880  *
881  * Type: be16.
882  * Maskable: bitwise.
883  * Formatting: hexadecimal.
884  * Prerequisites: none.
885  * Access: read/write.
886  * NXM: NXM_OF_VLAN_TCI(4) since v1.1.
887  * OXM: none.
888  * OF1.0: exact match.
889  * OF1.1: exact match.
890  */
891  MFF_VLAN_TCI,

1191  /* "ip_frag".
1192  *
1193  * IP fragment information.
1194  *
1195  * This field has three possible values:
1196  *
1197  * - A packet that is not an IP fragment has value 0.
1198  *
1199  * - A packet that is an IP fragment with offset 0 (the first fragment)
1200  * has bit 0 set and thus value 1.
1201  *
1202  * - A packet that is an IP fragment with nonzero offset has bits 0 and 1
1203  * set and thus value 3.
1204  *
1205  * NX_IP_FRAG_ANY and NX_IP_FRAG_LATER are declared to symbolically
1206  * represent the meanings of bits 0 and 1.
1207  *
1208  * The switch may reject matches against values that can never appear.
1209  *
1210  * It is important to understand how this field interacts with the OpenFlow
1211  * IP fragment handling mode:
1212  *
1213  * - In OFPC_FRAG_DROP mode, the OpenFlow switch drops all IP fragments
1214  * before they reach the flow table, so every packet that is available
1215  * for matching will have value 0 in this field.
1216  *
1217  * - Open vSwitch does not implement OFPC_FRAG_REASM mode, but if it did
1218  * then IP fragments would be reassembled before they reached the flow
1219  * table and again every packet available for matching would always
1220  * have value 0.
1221  *
1222  * - In OFPC_FRAG_NORMAL mode, all three values are possible, but
1223  * OpenFlow 1.0 says that fragments' transport ports are always 0, even
1224  * for the first fragment, so this does not provide much extra
1225  * information.
1226  *
1227  * - In OFPC_FRAG_NX_MATCH mode, all three values are possible. For
1228  * fragments with offset 0, Open vSwitch makes L4 header information
1229  * available.
1230  *
1231  * Type: u8 (low 2 bits).
1232  * Maskable: bitwise.
1233  * Formatting: frag.
1234  * Prerequisites: IPv4/IPv6.
1235  * Access: read-only.
1236  * NXM: NXM_NX_IP_FRAG(26) since v1.3.
1237  * OXM: none.
1238  */
